        "## 🔍 Post-Training Performance Analysis & Model Selection\n\n",
        "Based on the baseline evaluation matrix across the validation cohort, **Random Forest** has been officially selected as the project's **Champion Model** moving forward into the optimization phase. \n\n",
        "### Key Insights & Architectural Rationale:\n",
        "1. **Critical Clinical Recall ($1.0000$):** Both Random Forest and XGBoost achieved a flawless Recall score of 100%. In a diagnostic framework, this is the most vital metric as it signifies **zero False Negatives**—ensuring no high-risk malignant cases are missed.\n",
        "2. **Optimal Classification Balance:** Random Forest outperformed XGBoost and Logistic Regression by striking the highest overall harmony between feature filters, securing the dominant **Accuracy (0.9714)** and **F1-Score (0.9600)**.\n",
        "3. **High Threshold Stability:** A **ROC-AUC score of 0.9919** demonstrates that the Random Forest classifier possesses an incredibly stable probability threshold, making it highly reliable for downstream Explainable AI (XAI) biomarker tracking.\n\n",
        "### Next Phase: \n",
        "We will carry this Random Forest configuration into Week 4 for hyperparameter optimization (`GridSearchCV`) to fine-tune its precision boundary and eliminate minor false-alarm tendencies."
      ]
